<paragraph id="615D17532797AAE41986FC44A464FE02" pageId="111" pageNumber="112">
82. 
<taxonomicName id="B08AA1BD832F860659CC09D42CDD01F7" LSID="F20DB0EE-C84D-5E82-B2DD-6E0147E6DA93" authority="P. Silva &amp; Teles, Bol. Soc. Brot., ser. 2, 53: 515, t. 1. 1980. (Silva and Teles 1980: 515)." authorityName="P. Silva &amp; Teles, Bol. Soc. Brot., ser. 2, 53: 515, t. 1. 1980. (Silva and Teles" authorityYear="1980" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus fernandesii" order="Solanales" pageId="111" pageNumber="112" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fernandesii">Convolvulus fernandesii P.Silva &amp; Teles, Bol. Soc. Brot., ser. 2, 53: 515, t. 1. 1980. (Silva and Teles 1980: 515).</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3D6CCC58D6149334852907DBEFD0A73A" pageId="111" pageNumber="112" type="type">
<paragraph id="47E503F6180699262F98D642D6C71BF0" pageId="111" pageNumber="112">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3A3A110F3EE572DBA68998AD1315CA6B" pageId="111" pageNumber="112">
PORTUGAL, 
<emphasis id="61668995D5E16525DC12FA2AF62FA89C" italics="true" pageId="111" pageNumber="112">Pinto da Silva, Teles &amp; Pina</emphasis>
9337 (holotype LISE 94263!).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B3991BBDFCADEA76BC1529ED68E34F6A" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" type="description">
<paragraph id="7BBB2418ADA2411191CD9E24F61FE858" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">
<pageBreakToken id="D90323357574C204BC21F99E83E62718" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" start="start">Description</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="62005245A64274864541828D5E562246" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">
A scrambling or twining shrub, old stems woody, glabrescent, young stems pubescent. Leaves petiolate, 1-6 
<normalizedToken id="4CA3BC661A1A5012214CCF35254DFF42" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.5-3.5 cm, elliptic or oblong-elliptic, retuse, entire, base rounded to subcordate, puberulent on the nerves beneath but soon glabrescent; petiole 1-2.5 cm. Flowers 3-6 in axillary, pedunculate cymes; peduncles 1-2 cm; bracteoles 5-9 
<normalizedToken id="50285B2D658EF0998E48A507C28737FA" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-2.5 mm, oblanceolate; pedicels 5-10 mm; sepals 6-9 
<normalizedToken id="9C22A70D0123428B5D81C3C8AA8E9F06" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-3.5 mm, obovate to elliptic, mucronate, puberulent, inner sepals scarious, puberulent near base only; corolla 1.5-1.7 cm, white, sinuate, midpetaline bands tomentose; filaments glandular near base; ovary glabrous; style glabrous, divided c. 4 mm above base, stigmas c. 2 mm. Capsule and seeds unknown. [
<bibRefCitation id="F6DF3DA1C5F86A8B326273AA12D84BC2" author="Silvestre, S" editor="Talevera, S" journalOrPublisher="Real Jardin Botanico, CSIC, Madrid" pageId="211" pageNumber="212" pagination="252 - 273" refId="B337" refString="Silvestre, S, 2012. Convolvulus. In: Talevera, S, Andres, C, Arista, M, Fernandes Piedra, MP, Gallego, MJ, Ortiz, PL, Romero Zarco, C, Salgueiro, FJ, Silvestre, S, Quinanar, A, Eds., Flora Iberica volume 11: Gentianaceae to Boraginaceae. Real Jardin Botanico, CSIC, Madrid: 252 - 273" title="Convolvulus." volumeTitle="Flora Iberica volume 11: Gentianaceae to Boraginaceae." year="2012">Silvestre 2012</bibRefCitation>
: 260]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D2CC9B2C364674B468B674857BE59E66" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="38A789DEDABDA4EAD4DCB0D447FD540D" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AB810707CFB8E83E1A7359F838B61C2C" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Portugal: Cabo Espichel. Rare, narrow endemic of dolomitic rock at 125 m.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7F91AD0F1B34B9FA7191D91F50FFD873" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" type="notes">
<paragraph id="B491BEC19EC092E080339BA42BFE5A2C" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="76BB1965780F410AEDFE2EAAC02C785B" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Although seeds are clearly visible on the image of the type specimen no description has been provided.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="57D1E73A6BF0C5F628DD520AE48C1BD4" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">
This species is related to 
<taxonomicName id="C9CA0D36D32132CA8D81DA5CAE055A43" authorityName="L., Sp. Pl. 155. 1753. (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus canariensis" order="Solanales" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="canariensis">
<emphasis id="4DE1D316EDB1B1A25151C60208208BBE" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Convolvulus canariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and its allies from the Canary Islands and Madeira. It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="86ADF0FE61412162EA8FEA1495EE38C9" authorityName="L., Sp. Pl. 155. 1753. (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus canariensis" order="Solanales" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="canariensis">
<emphasis id="67D712CD530AB0CD2295A065FCDD91B3" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Convolvulus canariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its near glabrous leaves and from 
<taxonomicName id="B61CF0ED844413B3624A21A665AA2957" authorityName="F. Dietr., Nachtr. Vollst. Lex. Gaertn. 2: 377. 1816. (Dietrich" authorityYear="1816" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus massonii" order="Solanales" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="massonii">
<emphasis id="383EA263EA6F0651CBA8E85A0B124CE5" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Convolvulus massonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its shorter sepals, smaller corolla and glabrous ovary. It is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="85D3CD8119158E388DF8DD4B07C7BBFC" authorityName="Brouss. ex Link, Phys. Beschr. Canar. Ins. 145. 1828 [1825]. (Buch" authorityYear="1828" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus volubilis" order="Solanales" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="volubilis">
<emphasis id="4E9AB1290ADEEEA6553A749BB637DC2A" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Convolvulus volubilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but the leaves are oblong-elliptic, not linear lanceolate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
